"```sql\nSELECT \n    (COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE a.alignment = 'Good')::float / COUNT(*) * 100) AS percentage_good_superheroes\nFROM \n    superhero s\nJOIN \n    publisher p ON s.publisher_id = p.id\nJOIN \n    alignment a ON s.alignment_id = a.id\nWHERE \n    p.publisher_name = 'Marvel Comics';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of superheroes with a 'Good' alignment in Marvel Comics. It joins the `superhero`, `publisher`, and `alignment` tables to filter superheroes published by Marvel Comics and then computes the percentage of those with a 'Good' alignment."